gger's Later Philosophy''\n* Bastian Zimmermann, ''Die Offenbarung des Unverf\u00fcgbaren und die W\u00fcrde des Fragens. Ethische Dimensionen der Philosophie Martin Heideggers'' (London: 2010) {{ISBN|978-1-84790-037-1}}\n* [[Sean J. McGrath]] and [[Andrzej Wierci\u0144ski]], ed., ''A Companion to Heidegger\u2019s \"Phenomenology of Religious Life\"'' (Amsterdam: Rodopi, 2010).\n* Umberto Pagano, ''L'uomo senz'ombra. Elementi di sociologia dell'inautentico'' [https://books.google.com/books?id=Hnv7GjNo6OkC&printsec=frontcover&dq=umberto+pagano&hl=it&sa=X&ei=5LpOVPjsNOP9ygPWrYHYBA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=umberto%20pagano&f=false],(''The Man with no Shadow. Principles for a Sociology of Inauthenticity'') (Milan, 2007), [[FrancoAngeli]], {{ISBN|978-88-464-8523-6}}.\n\n===Reception in France===\n* [[Jean Beaufret]], ''Dialogue avec Heidegger'', 4 vols., Paris: Minuit, 1973\u20131985.\n* Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Courtine, ''Heidegger et la ph\u00e9nom\u00e9nologie'', Paris: Vrin, 1990.\n* John E. Drabinski and Eric S. Nelson, eds., ''Between Levinas and Heidegger'', Albany: SUNY Press, 2014.\n* [[Dominique Janicaud]], trans. Fran\u00e7ois Raffoul and David Pettigrew, [https://books.google.com/books?id=c_B9CwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''Heidegger en France''], 2 vols., Paris: [[\u00c9ditions Albin Michel|Albin Michel]], 2001.\n* [[Ethan Kleinberg]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=GlluDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''Generation Existential: Heidegger's Philosophy in France, 1927\u20131961'']\n* David Pettigrew and Fran\u00e7ois Raffoul, eds., [https://books.google.com/books?id=LHJEmHYctkcC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''French Interpretations of Heidegger: An Exceptional Reception''], Albany : SUNY Press, 2006.\n\n===Influence on Japanese philosophy===\n* Mayeda, Graham. 2006. ''Time, space and ethics in the philosophy of Watsuji Tetsur\u014d, Kuki Sh\u016bz\u014d, and Martin Heidegger'' (New York: Routledge, 2006). {{ISBN|0-415-97673-1}} (alk. paper).\n\n===Heidegger and Asian philosophy===\n* Parkes, Graham (1987). [https://books.google.com/books?id=bUa8ctgqeC8C&pg=PP1&dq=Heidegger+and+Asian+Thought  ''Heidegger and Asian Thought.''] Honolulu: University of Hawaii Press. {{ISBN|0-8248-1064-3}}\n* May, Reinhard, & Parkes, Graham (1996). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=KXKTY-adnTwC ''Heidegger's Hidden Sources: East Asian influences on his work'']. London: Routledge. {{ISBN|0-415-14037-4}}\n* Nelson, Eric S. (2017). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=SXUpDwAAQBAJ ''Chinese and Buddhist Philosophy in Early Twentieth-Century German Thought''] London: Bloomsbury. {{ISBN|9781350002555}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n===Archival collections===\n* [http://www.oac.cdlib.org/findaid/ark:/13030/tf6z09p138/ Guide to the Student Notes from Lectures by Martin Heidegger.] Special Collections and Archives, The UC Irvine Libraries, Irvine, California.\n* [http://www.beyng.com/ Works by Heidegger and on Heidegger (categorization)]\n* {{Helveticat}}\n\n===General information===\n* [http://www.lacan.com/symptom/?p=63 Political Texts - Rectoral Addresses]\n* [[W\u0142odzimierz Julian Korab-Karpowicz|W.J. Korab-Karpowicz]], [http://www.iep.utm.edu/heidegge/ Martin Heidegger (1889-1976)] in ''[[Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]''\n* [[Karl L\u00f6with]], [http://www.lacan.com/symptom/?p=55 My Last Meeting with Heidegger], Rome 1936\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20141220031453/http://www.heidegger-gesellschaft.de/ German Heidegger Society] {{in lang|de}}\n* Arne D. Naess, Jr., [http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/259513/Martin-Heidegger Martin Heidegger] in ''[[Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica]]''\n* Martin Heidegger, [http://www.lacan.com/heidespie.htm ''Der Spiegel'' Interview by Rudolf Augstein and Georg Wolff, 23 September 1966; published May 31 1976] \n* [http://www.weple.org/timeline.html#ids=14631,12007,12598,700,10671,9518,37304,95184,&title=8%20German%20Philosophers Timeline of German Philosophers]\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/31/books/heideggers-notebooks-renew-focus-on-anti-semitism.html?_r=0 Heidegger\u2019s Notebooks Renew Focus on Anti-Semitism]\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/007408}}\n\n===Works by Heidegger===\n* [http://think.hyperjeff.net/Heidegger English translations of Heidegger's works]\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Martin Heidegger}}\n\n{{Martin Heidegger}}\n{{continental philosophy}}\n{{Existentialism}}\n{{metaphysics}}\n{{Philosophy of mind}}\n{{Aesthetics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Heidegger, Martin}}\n[[Category:Martin Heidegger| ]]\n[[Category:1889 births]]\n[[Category:1976 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century German philosophers]]\n[[Category:Continental philosophers]]\n[[Category:Daseinsanalysis]]\n[[Category:Deaths from infectious disease]]\n[[Category:Enactive cognition]]\n[[Category:Existentialists]]\n[[Category:German fascists]]\n[[Category:German military personnel of World War I]]\n[[Category:German Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Hermeneutists]]\n[[Category:Nazi Party members]]\n[[Category:Nazis]]\n[[Category:Nietzsche scholars]]\n[[Category:Ontologists]]\n[[Category:People from Me\u00dfkirch]]\n[[Category:People from the Grand Duchy of Baden]]\n[[Category:Phenomenologists]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of art]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of culture]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of history]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of nihilism]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of technology]]\n[[Category:Political philosophers]]\n[[Category:University of Freiburg alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Freiburg faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Marburg faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Heidegger (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|German philosopher}}\n{{Infobox philosopher\n|region = [[Western philosophy]]\n|era   = [[20th-century philosophy]]\n|image = Heidegger 2 (1960).jpg\n|caption    = Heidegger in 1960\n|name       = 