     = Gender mainstreaming\n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| criminal_charges   = <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   =  \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters -->\n| mother             = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| father             = <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| relatives          = \n| family             = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n*Sadguru Gnananda Fellowship (2014),<ref>''Service and society'', Telangana First, September 16, 2014.[http://www.telanganafirst.in/?m=201409&paged=2]</ref>\n*Young Women Achiever Award (2011)<ref>Coreena Suares, ''The Wonder Women'', [[Deccan Chronicle]], 8 May 2012.[https://www.pressreader.com/india/deccan-chronicle/20120508/282497180682297]</ref>\n| website            = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n'''Shobha Gosa''' is a [[Women's activist]]<ref>''Panel discussion on \u2018Women Continue to Contribute to Social, Economic, Cultural and Political Achievement'', Indialogue Foundation, 2016.[http://indialogue.in/past-events/panel-discussion-on-women-continue-to-contribute-to-social-economic-cultural-and-political-achievement-and-indialogue-photo-story-contest-award-ceremony/]</ref> and leadership developer,<ref>''Bharat Yantra'', Volume 3, Issue 1, 2016-2017.[http://biet.ac.in/pdfs/Mech-newsletters2016-17.pdf]</ref> espousing the movement among youth<ref>Ranjan K Baruah, ''Gender mainstreaming workshop concludes'', Assam Times, July 17, 2015. [https://www.assamtimes.org/node/14260]</ref> towards women empowerment<ref>''Regional Action for Initiating Safety and Empowerment of Women in North East India'', North East Diocesan Social Service Society.[http://www.nedsf.net/gender.html]</ref> through sustained education.  She is also a person with interfaith understanding,<ref name=\"CB\">Catharine Buckell, ''Religion, violence and peace in India'', Utrecht University, Utrecht, 2011. [https://dspace.library.uu.nl/bitstream/handle/1874/206049/Catharine%20Buckell%20Bachelor%20Thesis.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y.]</ref> who has also contributed scientific papers.<ref>Leslie Nathaniel, Adrian Watkins (Edited), ''Gospel and Globalisation: 2nd South Asia Christian Youth Conference, 8-14 June 2005, Whitefield, Bangalore, India'', CMS/ISPCK, New Delhi, 2006, pp.179, 279.[https://books.google.co.in/books?id=-QTXAAAAMAAJ&dq=Gospel+and+Globalization+Watkins%2C+Nathaniel&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=gosa]</ref>\n==Education and Career==\nAfter her graduate education from [[Anantapur]] from the portals of [[Sri Krishnadevaraya University]], Shobha began her career with [[Non-governmental organisations in India]] in the [[New millennium]], notably, the Henry Martyn Institute,<ref name=\"CB\"/> [[Shivarampally]].<ref name=\"HMI\">''Interaction'', Volume 32, Number 2, July-December 2011, p.20.[https://docplayer.net/162201001-Interaction-index-page-3-editorial-pages-academic-programmes-pages-community-development-pages-conflict-transformation.html]</ref>  In 2012, she founded<ref>Madeleine Davies, ''Indians are a people of great faith and spirituality'', ''[[Church Times]]'', 17 August 2018.[https://www.churchtimes.co.uk/articles/2018/17-august/news/world/indians-are-a-people-of-great-faith-and-spirituality]</ref> Young People for Life India<ref>''Department of Commerce \u2013 Around India in 80 Minutes'', Villa Marie College, [https://villamariecollege.com/events/around-india-80-minutes/]</ref> as a registered Trust to achieve her vision of women empowerment.<ref>Valli Sarvani, ''Young People for Life India'', fusion.werindia, 2014.[https://fusion.werindia.com/unknown-wizards/young-people-for-life-india]</ref>\n==Recognition==\nShobha's espousal of causes through youth leadership, talent management, communication skills and behavioral management, as well as gender and\npeace building<ref>''Conversations Today'', Volume 2, Issue 8, August 2014, p.11.[http://csim.in/conversations/ConversationsToday-August2014.pdf]</ref> have been recognised over the past many years.<ref name=\"MSDS\"/>  In 2011, on the sidelines of United Nations International Women\u2019s Day Centenary Celebrations held by [[United Nations]], [[Government of Andhra Pradesh]] and State Institute of Rural Development in Hyderabad, she was awarded a Young Women Achiever Award<ref>Coreena Suares, ''The Wonder Women'', [[Deccan Chronicle]], 8 May 2012.[https://www.pressreader.com/india/deccan-chronicle/20120508/282497180682297]</ref> along with three other women.  In 2014,<ref name=\"MSDS\">''MSDS - Promoting Social Entrepreneurship in India'', Manava Seva Dharma Samvardhani, Chennai, 2016.[http://www.msdstrust.org/MSDS-Fellowship-2016.pdf]</ref> Shobha was a recipient of Sadguru Gnananda Fellowship<ref>''Service and society'', Telangana First, September 16, 2014.[http://www.telanganafirst.in/?m=201409&paged=2]</ref> awarded by a Chennai-based institution, Manava Seva Dharma Samvardhani.  The citation read,\n{{quote|''.....Founder, Young People for Life India working for the empowerment of youth in in Hyderabad through skill building and\ncounselling.''<ref name=\"MSDS\"/>}}\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite journal\n |author = \n |title  = Conversations Today\n |year   = August 2014\n |issue  = 8\n |isbn   = \n |url    = http://csim.in/conversations/ConversationsToday-August2014.pdf\n}}\n* {{cite journal\n |author = Catharine Buckell \n |title  = Religion, violence and peace in India\n |year   = 2011\n |issue  = \n |isbn   = \n |url    = https://dspace.library.uu.nl/bitstream/handle/1874/206049/Catharine%20Buckell%20Bachelor%20Thesis.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y.\n}}\n* {{cite journal\n |author = Leslie Nathaniel, Adrian Watkins (Edited)\n |title  = Gospel and Globalisation: 2nd South Asia Christian Youth Conference, 8-14 June 2005, Whitefield, Bangalore, India\n |year   = 2006\n |issue  = \n |isbn   = 8172149239\n |url    = https://books.google.co.in/books?id=-QTXAAAAMAAJ&dq=Gospel+and+Globalization+Watkins%2C+Nathaniel&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=isbn\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gosa, Shobha}}\n[[Category:Activists from Telangana]]\n[[Category:Telugu people]]\n[[Category:People from Telangana]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Indian women activists]]\n[[Category:Indian women's rights activists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian women]]\n{{India-activist-stub}}\n{{feminism-activist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = Ms.\n| name               = Shobha Gosa\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| image_upright      = \n| landscape          = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         = Shobha Rani Gosa\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year with {{Birth year and age|YYYY}} unless the exact date is already widely published, a