der}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-vac|last=[[Mikkel Kessler]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] European<br>[[super-middleweight]] champion\n|years=14 January 2012 \u2013 25 August 2012<br>Won world title}}\n{{s-vac|next=[[Geard Ajetovi\u0107]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-vac|last=[[Gilberto Ram\u00edrez]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=WBO International<br>super-middleweight champion\n|years=16 July 2016 \u2013 April 2017<br>Vacated}}\n{{s-vac|next=Himself}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-vac|last=Himself}}\n{{s-ttl|title=WBO International<br>super-middleweight champion\n|years=28 April 2018 \u2013 present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-text|style=background:#C1D8FF; font-weight: bold;|text=World boxing titles}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-vac|last=[[Jermain Taylor]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of IBF world champions#Middleweight|IBF middleweight champion]]\n|years=10 December 2005 \u2013 12 July 2009<br>Vacated}}\n{{s-vac|next=[[Sebastian Sylvester]]}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Robert Stieglitz]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of WBO world champions#Super middleweight|WBO super-middleweight champion]]\n|years=25 August 2012 \u2013 23 March 2013}}\n{{s-aft|after=Robert Stieglitz}}\n{{s-ttl|title=WBO super-middleweight champion\n|years=1 March 2014 \u2013 [[Manny Pacquiao vs. Timothy Bradley III|9 April 2016]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Gilberto Ram\u00edrez]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abraham, Arthur}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Armenian male boxers]]\n[[Category:Middleweight boxers]]\n[[Category:Super-middleweight boxers]]\n[[Category:German Armenians]]\n[[Category:World middleweight boxing champions]]\n[[Category:World super-middleweight boxing champions]]\n[[Category:International Boxing Federation champions]]\n[[Category:World Boxing Organization champions]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Yerevan]]\n[[Category:German male boxers]]\n[[Category:Armenian emigrants to Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Armenian boxer}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n| name = Arthur Abraham<br>{{small|\u0531\u057e\u0565\u057f\u056b\u0584 \u0531\u0562\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0574\u0575\u0561\u0576}}\n| image = Arthur Abraham open workout.jpg\n| caption = Abraham in 2010\n| realname = Avetik Abrahamyan\n| nickname = {{plainlist|\n*King Arthur\n*Abrahammer\n}}\n| weight = {{plainlist|\n*[[Middleweight]]\n*[[Super-middleweight]]\n}}\n| height = 1.75 m<ref>{{boxRec|id=208432}}. Retrieved 17 July 2017.</ref>\n| reach = 183 cm\n| nationality = {{plainlist|\n*Armenian\n*German\n}}\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|2|20|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenian SSR]],<br>Soviet Union\n| style = [[Orthodox stance|Orthodox]]\n| total = 53\n| wins = 47\n| KO = 30\n| losses = 6\n| draws = \n| no contests = \n}}\n\n'''Avetik Abrahamyan''' ({{lang-hy|\u0531\u057e\u0565\u057f\u056b\u0584 \u0531\u0562\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0574\u0575\u0561\u0576}}; born 20 February 1980), best known as '''Arthur Abraham''', is an Armenian-German [[professional boxer]]. He is a multiple-time former world champion in two [[weight class (boxing)|weight classes]], having held the [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] [[middleweight]] title from 2005 to 2009 with successful defenses against ten boxers (the third most in middleweight history), and the [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] [[super-middleweight]] title twice between 2012 and 2016.\n\n==Early life==\nAvetik Abrahamyan was born in [[Yerevan]], [[Soviet Armenia]] on 20 February 1980 to parents Grigor and Sylvia Abrahamyan.<ref>[http://arthur.eeedv.de/de/node/20 Portrait von Arthur Abraham | Offizielle Website von Arthur Abraham]. Arthur.eeedv.de (2011-08-18). Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref> He moved to Germany with his parents and brothers in 1995 at the age of 15. As a teenager, Abraham showed an interest in [[cycling]] and eventually became the North [[Bavaria]]n and [[Franconia]]n Youth Champion.<ref name=\"sauerland discovered\">{{cite news |title=Sauerland Explains How Arthur Abraham Was Discovered |url=https://www.boxinginsider.com/headlines/sauerland-explains-how-arthur-abraham-was-discovered/ |work=BoxingInsider.com |date=10 August 2009 |access-date=4 December 2011}}</ref> However, after watching an exciting [[Mike Tyson]] fight, Arthur was inspired to become a boxing star too.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Vester |first1=Mark |last2=Schlabe |first2=Thomas |date=9 October 2009 |title=Arthur Abraham Inspired To Fight By Mike Tyson |url=https://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-inspired-fight-by-mike-tyson--22724 |work=Boxing Scene |access-date=7 December 2011}}</ref> In 1999, Arthur and his brothers returned to Armenia for military service. After 2002, all the brothers had finished their military service and returned to Germany in 2003.<ref name=\"aawcbym\">{{cite news |title=Arthur Abraham: A World Champion Boxer, But Every Bit a Typical Young Man |url=http://asbarez.com/54099/arthur-abraham-a-world-champion-boxer-but-every-bit-a-typical-young-man/ |work=[[Asbarez]] |date=21 October 2006 |access-date=4 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Shahbazyan |first=Lusine |date=28 January 2017 |title=Arthur Abraham: I am proud that I was soldier of triumphant Armenian Army |url=https://sport.news.am/eng/news/75143/arthur-abraham-i-am-proud-that-i-was-soldier-of-triumphant-armenian-army.html |work=NEWS.am Sport |access-date=28 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Amateur career==\nAbraham boxed as an [[amateur boxing|amateur]] in [[Bamberg]] and later in [[Nuremberg]]. He was an International [[junior welterweight]] German champion in 1997 and a three time Senior [[light middleweight]] Armenian champion in 2000, 2001 and 2002.<ref name=\"sauerland discovered\"/><ref name=\"aawcbym\"/> Abraham attempted to compete for Armenia at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]], but was unable due to his two years of military service. In 2003, with Arthur and his brother Alexander returned to Germany, hoping to begin a professional boxing career.<ref name=\"sauerland discovered\"/> His final amateur record was 81-3-6 (48 KO).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sauerlandpromotion.com/profiles/arthur-abraham/|title=Arthur 'King Arthur' Abraham - Sauerland Promotions|website=www.sauerlandpromotion.com|access-date=2018-01-14}}</ref>\n\nIn 2003, Arthur and Alexander competed alongside promoter and manager [[Wilfried Sauerland]] and his head coach [[Ulli Wegner]]. Arthur was a sparring partner for [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] and [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] [[super middleweight]] champion [[Sven Ottke]], whom was in the preparations of a title defense. Wegner was so impressed that he began to train Arthur personally.<ref name=\"sauerland discovered\"/><ref name=\"aawcbym\"/>\n\n===Amateur highlights===\n* 1997 International [[light-welterweight]] German champion\n* 2000, 2001 and 2002 Senior [[light-middleweight]] Armenian champion\n\n==Professional career==\n===Middleweight===\n====Early career====\nAbraham started his professional career on 16 August 2003. The [[Wilfried Sauerland|Sauerland]]-promoted Abraham had many early victories.<ref name=\"sauerland discovered\"/> He defeated Canadian southpaw [[Ian Gardner]] (18\u20131) for the vacant [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] Inter-Continental [[middleweight]] title, [[Hector Velazco]] (former [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] champion) and contender Nader Hamdan (36\u20131).<ref>{{cite news |title=German NDR TV Channel shooting movie dedicated to Arthur Abraham |url=https://armenpress.am/eng/news/762328/german-ndr-tv-channel-shooting-movie-dedicated-to-arthur-abraham.html |work=[[Armenpress]] |date=19 May 2014 |access-date=19 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2005, Abraham defended his WBA Inter-Continental title against the highly regarded Briton [[Howard Eastman]]. Eastman had previously only lost to American [[William Joppy]] and former [[Undisputed Champion|Undisputed]] middleweight champion [[Bernard Hopkins]].<ref>{{Citation|last=HAY TV|title=Arthur Abraham vs Howard Eastman|date=2017-01-16|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s8C-oUMp7QU|accessdate=2018-01-14}}</ref>\n\n===IBF middleweight champion===\n\n==== Abraham vs. Ikeke ====\nOn 10 December 2005, in [[Leipzig]], Germany, Abraham won the vacant [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] [[List of middleweight boxing champions|middleweight]] title against [[Kingsley Ikeke]] (23-1, 13 KOs) by a 5th round knock-out.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxing247.com/weblog/archives/106339|title=IBF Middleweight Championship Arthur Abraham vs. Kingsley Ikeke \u2022 Boxing News|date=2005-11-04|work=Boxing News Archive|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-US}}</ref> The IBF belt had previously been vacated by undisputed champion [[Jermain Taylor]] after a bout with Abraham was denied in October that year. In the fifth round, Arthur met Ikeke with hard shots to the head. Ikeke began to tumble toward the canvas and Abraham landed some final rights to seal the victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxnews.com.ua/en/news/2244/2005-12-11/rss|title=Arthur Abraham deposes Kingsley Ikeke \u2013 World boxing \u2013 Boxing news \u2013 BOXNEWS.com.ua|website=www.boxnews.com.ua|access-date=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=2255039|title=Abraham stops Ikeke to win IBF middleweight title|date=2005-12-10|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\nAbraham defended his title on 5 March 2006 with a unanimous decision against Australian [[Shannan Taylor]]. Two months later, Abraham won a second title defense against [[Kofi Jantuah]], also on points.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/media/index.php?title=Fight:1045998|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Shannan Taylor|last=|first=|date=|website=boxrec.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-07-25}}</ref>\n\n==== Abraham vs. Miranda ====\nOn 23 September 2006, Abraham won a decision against undefeated contender [[Edison Miranda]] despite having his jaw broken in two places in round four. Miranda took advantage of this by fighting dirty. Miranda was docked five points for landing repeated low blows as well as intentionally headbutting Abraham. However, even without the five points deducted, Abraham would have still won the fight (114-109, 115-109, 116-109).<ref>{{cite news |last=Persson |first=Per Ake |date=23 September 2006 |title=Abraham Beats Miranda in Wild Fight |url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-beats-miranda-wild-fight--5619 |work=Boxing Scene |access-date=23 September 2016}}</ref> Abraham's jaw was operated on the night after the fight. He had 22 screws inserted into two titanium plates. After the Miranda bout, Arthur was praised for his ability to finish the fight despite his injury.\n\nAbraham defeated Canadian [[S\u00e9bastien Demers]] by KO in the third round after two minutes and fifty-seven seconds. Abraham was clearly physically superior than his opponent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allthebestfights.com/arthur-abraham-vs-demers-video-full-fight-pelea/|title=Arthur Abraham vs Sebastien Demers \u2013 full fight Video IBF title|date=2011-04-27|work=All The Best Fights.com|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-GB}}</ref> Arthur won his fifth title defense by defeating fellow Armenian [[Khoren Gevor]] by 11th-round knockout from a powerful left hook.<ref>{{Citation|last=chrissgd|title=Boxing \u2013 A. Abraham vs. K. Gevor  \u2013 knockout|date=2007-08-18|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kiGTFPRQbLU|accessdate=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allthebestfights.com/abraham-vs-gevor-video-full-fight-pelea/|title=Video \u2013 Arthur Abraham vs Khoren Gevor \u2013 full fight video IBF|date=2011-04-26|work=All The Best Fights.com|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==== Abraham vs. Elcock, Ayala ====\nOn 8 December 2007, Abraham defeated [[Wayne Elcock]] to make his sixth title defense by technical knockout in the 5th round.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/boxing/7062511.stm|title=Elcock earns fight with Abraham|date=2007-10-25|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxing247.com/weblog/archives/116035/amp/|title=Arthur Abraham vs Wayne Elcock on December 8 \u2022 Boxing News|date=2007-10-25|work=Boxing News Archive|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x59zzr|title=Boxing \u2013 Arthur Abraham vs. Wayne Elcock \u2013 Video Dailymotion|date=2008-05-01|website=Dailymotion|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>\n\nDuring two of his matches, Abraham was accompanied by live performances of the [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]] and is currently accompanied by the track \"Ready For The Fight\" by [[The Young Punx]].\n\nOn 29 March 2008, Abraham defeated American [[Elvin Ayala]] via 12th-round KO after connecting with a devastating left hook that sent his opponent crashing to the canvas face first. This was Abraham's 7th successful title defence.<ref>{{Citation|last=serob yenok|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Elvin Ayala|date=2008-07-15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kuIqdmsduSQ|accessdate=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2008/3/30/55619/8200|title=Arthur Abraham drops Elvin Ayala in Germany|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>\n\n====Abraham vs. Miranda II====\n[[File:Arthur-Abraham-mit-WM-G\u00fcrtel.jpg|thumb|Abraham with the [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] [[middleweight]] title, 2008]]\nOn 21 June 2008, a rematch between Abraham and Miranda took place at a [[catchweight]] of 166&nbsp;lbs. Abraham's IBF middleweight title was not on the line. In the first minute of the fourth round, a perfectly timed right hand-left hook sent Miranda to the floor. Miranda rose, clearly hurt. Another left hook would drop Miranda along the ropes and Miranda would again rise but his legs were clearly gone and the end was at hand. Abraham landed a final striking right hand for the round's third knockdown as the referee leapt in to halt the action before Miranda could attempt to rise again.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fightreport.net/?p=820|title=Abraham fights through broken jaw to defend his IBF middleweight title|date=2006-09-24|newspaper=Fight Report|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-30|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031090541/http://www.fightreport.net/?p=820|archivedate=2016-10-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Abraham batters Miranda |url=http://www.espn.com/espn/wire?section=boxing&id=3455860 |work=ESPN |date=22 June 2008 |access-date=22 June 2008}}</ref>\n\n====Abraham vs. Marquez====\nOn 8 November 2008, Abraham defeated [[Ra\u00fal M\u00e1rquez]] (41\u20134\u20131, 29 KOs), 37, by a 6th round [[technical knockout]], at the [[Bamberg]]'s [[Jako]] Arena, the 8th defense of his IBF middleweight boxing title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-vs-raul-marquez-slated-october-4--15151|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Raul Marquez Slated For October 4 - Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|access-date=2016-10-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/sports/boxing/2008-11-08-3033146276_x.htm|title=Abraham defeats Marquez to defend IBF title - USATODAY.com|website=usatoday30.usatoday.com|access-date=2016-10-30}}</ref>\n\nHe retained his IBF title on 14 March 2009 against [[Lajuan Simon]], his first fight over 12 rounds since his legendary battle against Edison Miranda.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2009/3/16/798748/arthur-abraham-v-lajuan-si|title=Arthur Abraham v. Lajuan Simon \u2013 Full Fight|date=2009-03-16|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> The 10th and final defense of his middleweight title took place in Berlin against [[Mahir Oral]]. Abraham won this fight by a 10th-round technical knockout. Oral's coach threw in the towel after several knockdowns.<ref>{{Citation|last=catasyou|title=Arthur Abraham vs Mahir Oral|date=2012-04-23|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nRSFGERxsfY|accessdate=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\n===Super-middleweight===\n====Super Six World Boxing Classic====\n{{Main article|Super Six World Boxing Classic}}\nAfter failing to secure a match-up with [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] and [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] champion [[Kelly Pavlik]] or [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] champion [[Felix Sturm]], Abraham announced that he would change his weight class to compete at [[super middleweight]]. Abraham participated in the [[Super Six World Boxing Classic]] tournament for the [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] and [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] super middleweight titles. Fellow participants were: WBA champion [[Mikkel Kessler]], WBC champion [[Carl Froch]], [[Andre Dirrell]], [[Andre Ward]] and [[Jermain Taylor]].\n\n===== Abraham vs. Taylor =====\nIn his first match of the tournament, Abraham faced [[Jermain Taylor]] on 17 October 2009. Arthur was previously supposed to fight Taylor for the undisputed middleweight title, but the fight fell through. Abraham defeated Taylor via a devastating knockout in the 12th round. Taylor was hospitalized with a severe concussion, suffering short term memory loss, unable to remember details of this bout. Taylor was replaced with veteran [[Allan Green]] in the tournament. After being released from the hospital, Taylor released a statement saying that he's doing just fine and wanted to congratulate Abraham on his victory and wish him well in the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/boxing/6367380/Jermain-Taylor-hospitalised-after-knock-out-from-Arthur-Abraham.html|title=Jermain Taylor hospitalised after knock-out from Arthur Abraham|last=Correspondent|first=By Gareth A Davies, Boxing|work=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en}}</ref> Former [[heavyweight]] champion [[Mike Tyson]] was in attendance and was impressed by Abraham's intensity and determination.<ref>[http://www.boxinginsider.com/headlines/abrahams-intensity-determination-impress-mike-tyson/ Abraham\u2019s Intensity & Determination Impress Mike Tyson | BoxingInsider.com \u2013 Boxing | Boxing News]. BoxingInsider.com (2009-10-27). Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://lasvegassun.com/news/2009/oct/17/arthur-abraham-knocks-out-jermain-taylor-final-rou/|title=Arthur Abraham knocks out Jermain Taylor in final round|date=2009-10-17|work=LasVegasSun.com|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>\n\nAs of the end of 2009, ''[[The Ring (magazine)|The Ring]]'' has ranked Abraham as the 14th best boxer in the world.<ref>[http://www.ringtv.com/blog/1482/the_ring_top_100_125/ The Ring Top 100 | Ringtv.craveonline.com | Blog] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100119073201/http://www.ringtv.com/blog/1482/the_ring_top_100_125/ |date=January 19, 2010 }}. Ringtv.craveonline.com. Retrieved on 2012-01-16.</ref> On 5 March 2010, Abraham was ranked #8 in the world by [[Yahoo! Sports]].<ref>Iole, Kevin. (2010-03-05) [https://sports.yahoo.com/box/news?slug=ki-abraham030510 Unbeaten Abraham seeks U.S. stardom \u2013 Boxing \u2013 Yahoo! Sports]. Sports.yahoo.com. Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref>\n\n===== Abraham vs. Dirrell =====\nOn 27 March 2010, Abraham fought American boxer [[Andre Dirrell]] in the second stage of the Super Six World Boxing Classic at the [[Joe Louis Arena]] in Detroit, Michigan. At the end of round 10, Dirrell was comfortably ahead 97\u201392, 98\u201391 and 97\u201392 on the scorecards. In round 10, Abraham knocked Dirrell down following a straight right, but the referee ruled it a slip. Abraham lost via disqualification due to hitting Dirrell after he slipped in the 11th round. Dirrell slipped after being hit on the chin near the corner. The fight was stopped at 1:13 of the round. After he slipped, Abraham landed a right hand to his chin, knocking him down and out completely. Through a translator, Abraham said, \"I was not looking at his feet, I was looking at his eyes. I didn't see if he was down.\" After the punch, the ring immediately filled up with people including Andre's brother [[Anthony Dirrell|Anthony]]. Andre was taken to hospital for a [[Neuroimaging|brain scan]]. Anthony later confirmed that his brother was alright. Abraham suffered his first defeat professionally due to the disqualification.<ref>[http://www.fightnews.com/?p=41279 Boxing \u2013 More on Dirrell-Abraham] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329145954/http://www.fightnews.com/?p=41279 |date=2010-03-29 }}. Fightnews.com (2010-03-28). Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/boxing/8591725.stm|title=BBC Sport \u2013 Andre Dirrell defeats Arthur Abraham in Super Six bout|website=news.bbc.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=5034741|title=Dirrell beats Abraham on disqualification in 11th|date=2010-03-28|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>\n\n===== Abraham vs. Froch =====\nAbraham was next scheduled to fight British boxer [[Carl Froch]] (26-1, 20 KOs), also for the vacant WBC super middleweight title on 27 November 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/boxing/sport/story/47102.html|title=Froch to face Abraham on November 27 in Helsinki|work=ESPN.co.uk|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/boxing/sport/story/49152.html|title=Froch to fight for WBC title against Abraham|work=ESPN.co.uk|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-GB}}</ref> The fight was pushed back from 2 October in Monaco due to Froch suffering a back injury.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thesweetscience.com/articles-of-2010/11397-froch-vs-abraham-lands-in-monaco|title=Froch vs Abraham Lands In Monaco \u2013 The Sweet Science|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=5384615|title=Froch, Abraham find middle ground in Monaco|date=2010-07-16|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> The fight took place at the [[Hartwall Arena]] in [[Helsinki|Helsinki, Finland]]. Abraham failed to become a two-weight world champion, losing to Froch in his third fight of the tournament. Abraham was dominated from start to finish, losing by a unanimous decision. The scores given by the judges were 119\u2013109, 120\u2013108 and 120\u2013108, which reflected the one-sided nature of the bout. Abraham was disappointed with his performance, \"I wanted to hit him. I tried but I could not do it. Nothing more to say.\" Froch stated it was his best performance to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=5857146|title=Froch wins, claims WBC super middleweight title|date=2010-11-28|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/boxing/9226185.stm|title=BBC Sport \u2013 Carl Froch beats Arthur Abraham to win back WBC belt|website=news.bbc.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2010/11/27/1839263/super-six-results-from-helsinki-carl-froch-v-arthur-abraham|title=Carl Froch Shuts Out Arthur Abraham Over 12 Rounds|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>\n\n===== Abraham vs. Ward =====\nAbraham qualified for the semifinals, having one win out of three fights. But first, Abraham had a pre-fight with [[Croatia]]n contender [[Stjepan Bo\u017ei\u0107]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingnews24.com/2011/01/arthur-abraham-vs-stjepan-bozic-on-212/|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Stjepan Bozic on 2/12 \u00bb Boxing News|date=2011-01-16|work=Boxing News 24|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref> Abraham won by technical knockout in the second round due to an injury in Bo\u017ei\u0107's hand.<ref>{{Citation|last=humax1956|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Stjepan Bozic|date=2011-02-12|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oBe3yo1q7kA|accessdate=2017-07-17}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 May 2011, Abraham fought undefeated American [[Andre Ward]] in the Super Six semi finals for the WBA super middleweight title. The fight took place at the [[Home Depot Center]] in [[Carson, California]]. Abraham entered having lost two of his previous three bouts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxinginsider.com/headlines/super-6-semi-finals-andre-ward-vs-arthor-abraham/|title=Super 6 Semi Finals, Andre Ward vs Arthor Abraham  {{!}} BoxingInsider.com|date=2011-03-22|work=BoxingInsider.com|access-date=2017-09-22|language=en-US}}</ref> Ward started out slow with Abraham, trying to find a way to penetrate his tight defense. After a competitive first few rounds, Ward seized control of the fight, using his ring savvy and instincts to control Abraham. Although Abraham was somewhat passive at times, he gave an earnest effort and frequently threw combinations that were mostly blocked by Ward. Abraham hurt Ward a couple of times in the final round, but it wasn't enough to finish Ward, who had dominated the fight and won a lopsided unanimous decision. The three judges scored the bout 120-108, 118-110 & 118-111. ESPN had it 118-110 in favor of Ward. Abraham didn't believe he had lost the fight with such wide scores. Over 12 rounds, Ward threw 289 jabs. In total he landed 178 of 444 total punches thrown (40%).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2011/5/15/2171646/andre-ward-vs-arthur-abraham-results-super-six-showtime-boxing-ne|title=Andre Ward Takes Wide Decision Win Over Arthur Abraham|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-09-22}}</ref> Ward went on to defeat Froch in the finals and won the [[Super Six World Boxing Classic]] tournament.\n\n===Comeback===\nOn 30 October 2011, Abraham originally announced that he intended to return to the middleweight division in 2012<ref>[http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-middleweight-run-starts-january--45495 Arthur Abraham: Middleweight Run Starts in January \u2013 Boxing News]. Boxingscene.com. Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref> but later decided to remain at super middleweight.<ref>[http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-stay-168-eyes-stieglitzs-wbo-title--48664 Arthur Abraham Will Stay at 168, Eyes Stieglitz's WBO Title \u2013 Boxing News]. Boxingscene.com. Retrieved on 2012-03-27.</ref>\n\nIn his first comeback fight on 14 January 2012, Abraham defeated Argentinian Pablo Oscar Natalio Farias via technical knockout in round five and won the vacant [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] European super middleweight championship. After Abraham landed several hard combinations that put Farias down three times in the fifth round, referee Manuel Maritxalar stopped the fight.<ref>[http://www.hyefighters.com/2012/01/14/hyefighter-abraham-kos-farias/ HyeFighter Abraham KO\u2019s Farias \u2013 Hyefighters.com]. HyeFighters.com. Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-returns-stops-pablo-farias-five--48543|title=Arthur Abraham Returns, Stops Pablo Farias in Five|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> On 31 March 2012, Abraham defeated former [[European Boxing Union|EBU]] super middleweight champion [[Piotr Wilczewski]] by a lopsided unanimous decision to retain his WBO European title. Wilczewski was docked a point in the seventh round and was down in the eleventh round, though it was ruled a slip.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-decisions-wilczewski-eyes-wbo-title--51262|title=Arthur Abraham Decisions Wilczewski, Eyes WBO Title|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\n===WBO super-middleweight champion===\n====Abraham vs. Stieglitz====\nIn April 2012, the WBO announced that they had removed [[George Groves (boxer)|George Groves]] as their [[mandatory challenger]] and replaced him with Abraham, meaning the latter would now be in line to challenge [[List of WBO world champions#Super middleweight|WBO super middleweight]] champion [[Robert Stieglitz]] (41-2, 23 KOs). Sauerland Event confirmed the fight would take place on 25 August in Berlin at the [[Mercedes-Benz Arena (Berlin)|O2 World]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/groves-bounced-abraham-new-mandatory-stieglitz--51909|title=Groves Bounced, Abraham The New Mandatory To Stieglitz|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-14|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-vs-stieglitz-battle-land-on-august-25th--52619|title=Abraham vs Stieglitz Battle Might Land on August 25th|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-14|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-robert-stieglitz-o2-world-8-25-berlin--53214|title=Arthur Abraham-Robert Stieglitz: O2 World, 8/25 in Berlin|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-14|language=en-us}}</ref> Abraham won a twelve-round unanimous decision over Stieglitz to capture the WBO championship in a spectacular battle which made Abraham a two-division champion. Abraham became the second Armenian and the first German to win championships in two different divisions. The judges' scores were 116-112, 116-112 and 115-113.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ringtv.craveonline.com/blog/174449-abraham-outpoints-stieglitz-wins-wbo-super-middleweight-belt |title=Abraham outpoints Stieglitz, wins WBO super middleweight belt |last=Coppinger |first=Mike |date=25 August 2012 |publisher=RingTV |access-date=31 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120829022255/http://ringtv.craveonline.com/blog/174449-abraham-outpoints-stieglitz-wins-wbo-super-middleweight-belt |archivedate=29 August 2012 }}</ref> Abraham was named best boxer of Germany in 2012 by ''BoxSport'' magazine. His coach [[Ulli Wegner]] was also named the best coach of the year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arthur Abraham Named Boxer of The Year By BoxSport |url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-named-boxer-year-by-boxsport--60740 |work=Boxing Scene |date=22 December 2012 |access-date=31 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n====Abraham vs. Bouadla, Stieglitz II ====\nOn 9 October 2012 [[Mehdi Bouadla]] (26-4-0, 11 KOs) was confirmed as Abraham's first title defence at super middleweight. The fight took place on 15 December at [[Arena N\u00fcrnberger Versicherung|N\u00fcremberg Arena]], [[Nuremberg|N\u00fcremberg, Germany]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sport.news.am/eng/news/16165/|title=Arthur Abraham to face Mehdi Bouadla {{!}} NEWS.am Sport \u2013 All about sports|website=sport.news.am|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kwese.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/8482182/arthur-abraham-make-first-defense-super-middleweight-title-mehdi-bouadla-germany|title=Abraham set to defend title against Bouadla|publisher=ESPN|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> Abraham retained his title against Bouadla on 15 December 2012. He won via technical knockout in the eighth round. A cut beside Bouadla's right eye streamed blood into his eyes, impeding his vision and causing the stoppage of the bout, as he could not see Abraham's punches and as such took brutal punishment. In the post fight, Abraham said, \"This is where I started boxing. To be here now, in front of 10,000 people as world champion -- there's no better feeling.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Arthur Abraham retains WBO belt |url=http://espn.go.com/boxing/story/_/id/8750594/arthur-abraham-stops-mehdi-bouadla-retain-wbo-crown |work=ESPN |date=15 December 2012 |access-date=31 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2012/12/15/3771096/abraham-vs-bouadla-results-arthur-retains-wbo-title-eighth-round-tko-boxing-news|title=Abraham stops Bouadla in eight, retains title|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\nFive days after the Bouadia fight, a rematch with Stieglitz was discussed to take place in the first quarter of 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-vs-stieglitz-rematch-eyed-possibly-april-9--60687|title=Abraham vs. Stieglitz Rematch Eyed, Possibly April 9|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> In January, Abraham stated the fight would take place on 3 March. At the time, Stieglitz was entering a legal dispute after allegedly assaulting his father-in-law, which he stated was self-defence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-robert-stieglitz-rematch-on-march-23--61761|title=Arthur Abraham-Robert Stieglitz Rematch on March 23?|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> The fight took place in Stieglitz's home of [[Magdeburg]], [[Saxony-Anhalt|Sachsen-Anhalt]], Germany in front of 8,000 at the [[GETEC Arena]]. Abraham's eye rapidly swelled shut in the second round and he could soon no longer see. The referee waved him off at the start of the fourth round, resulting in his defeat.<ref>{{cite news |last=Thomas |first=Rich |date=25 March 2013 |title=Did Robert Stiegtlitz head butt his way to victory over Arthur Abraham? |url=http://www.proboxing-fans.com/did-robert-stiegtlitz-head-butt-his-way-to-victory-over-arthur-abraham_032513/ |work=ProBoxing-Fans.com |access-date=25 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/stieglitz-stops-abraham-avenge-loss-regain-title--63672|title=Stieglitz Stops Abraham To Avenge Loss, Regain Title|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> CompuBox stats showed that Stieglitz was in full control of the rematch, landing 70 of 203 punches thrown (34%), with Abraham landed 27 of his 107 thrown (25%). Stieglitz out-landed Abraham 63-19 in power punches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/forums/view.php?pg=stieglitz-abraham-rematch-compubox|title=Stieglitz vs. Abraham - CompuBox Stats|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>\n\n===Regaining composure===\nAfter losing the World title, Abraham had two more fights in 2013. First he beat [[Willbeforce Shihepo]] (20-4, 15 KOs) by 12 round unanimous decision (116-113, 117-111 & 116-112). Abraham claimed the vacant WBO Inter-Continenteal super middleweight title.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2013/8/24/4655136/boxing-results-braehmer-routs-abatangelo-abraham-struggles-with|title=Results: Braehmer wins, Abraham scrapes by|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> Two months later, Abraham successfully defended the title against [[Giovanni De Carolis]] (20-4, 10 KOs) by unanimous decision (120-108, 119-109 twice).<ref>{{Citation|last=MrGiudizio|title=Arthur Abraham vs Giovanni De Carolis|date=2013-10-26|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ak4iR3Kc_io|accessdate=2017-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingnews24.com/2013/10/arthur-abraham-vs-giovanni-de-carolis-this-saturday-in-germany/|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Giovanni De Carolis this Saturday in Germany \u00bb Boxing News|date=2013-10-21|work=Boxing News 24|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxnation.com/boxing-matches/arthur-abraham-v-giovanni-de-carolis/|title=Boxing Matches : Arthur Abraham v Giovanni De Carolis : BoxNation|website=www.boxnation.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\n===WBO super-middleweight champion===\n====Abraham vs. Stieglitz III, Sjekloca====\nA rubber match with Stieglitz (46-3, 26 KOs) took place on 1 March 2014, with the [[World Boxing Organisation|WBO]] [[super middleweight]] title on the line once again at the [[GETEC Arena]] in [[Magdeburg]], Germany. After a purse bid was ordered where the minimum bid was $300,000, Stieglitz promoter Ulf Steinforth of SES bid $3,135,000 on 9 December, easily beating the other bid, which came from Abraham's promoter Sauerland Event at $1,541,414. Stieglitz, being the champion was entitled to $2,351,250 (75%), while Abraham would receive the remaining $783,750 (25%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/boxing/story/_/id/10103706/robert-stieglitz-arthur-abraham-fight-march-3rd|title=Robert Stieglitz, Arthur Abraham to fight in March for 3rd time|publisher=ESPN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/ses-wins-purse-bid-stieglitz-abraham-rubber-match--72525|title=SES Wins Purse Bid For Stieglitz-Abraham Rubber Match|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> In a very close fight through 11 rounds, Stieglitz took a knee in the twelfth round, as Abraham's counter-punching took its toll. Stieglitz was the 'come forward' aggressor with jab attacks. Abraham fought with counterattacks that wore Stieglitz down late. Abraham won the fight by split decision (112-113, 114-111 & 115-110).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/photo-abraham-stieglitz-3-judges-agree-on-most-rounds--75235|title=Photo: Abraham-Stieglitz 3 - Judges Agree on Most Rounds|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2014/3/1/5461258/stieglitz-vs-abraham-iii-results-arthur-abraham-wins-split-decision+&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk|title=Abraham regains WBO title from Stieglitz|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/boxing/2014/03/01/abraham-beats-stieglitz-for-wbo-super-middle-belt/5932333/|title=Arthur Abraham beats Robert Stieglitz for WBO belt|work=USA TODAY|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-drops-defeats-stieglitz-reclaim-his-title--75168|title=Abraham Drops, Defeats Stieglitz To Reclaim His Title|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> CompuBox stats showed that Abraham landed 140 of 451 punches thrown (31%), Stieglitz landed 106 of his 489 (22%). Abraham was much more active in the final 5 rounds and worked his jab, which was the key to winning the fight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/forums/view.php?pg=abraham-stieglitz-triilogy-compubox|title=Abraham-Stieglitz 3 - CompuBox|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>\n\nIn April, Abraham planned a quick first defence to be made two months later against Serbian [[Nikola Sjeklo\u0107a|Nikola Sjekloca]] (28-1, 8 KOs). The fight took place at [[Velodrom (Berlin)|Velodrom]] in Berlin, Germany on 3 May 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-nikola-sjekloca-set-down-3--75768|title=Arthur Abraham-Nikola Sjekloca Set Down for May 3 \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2014/3/18/5522974/arthur-abraham-to-make-first-title-defense-on-may-3-against-nikola+&cd=13&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk|title=Abraham-Sjekloca done for May 3|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/10628296/arthur-abraham-defend-title-nikola-sjekloca|title=Abraham to put belt on line against Sjekloca|publisher=ESPN|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref> The fight went full 12 rounds as Abraham came out victorious on points on all three judges scorecards (116-112, 116-113, 119-110). Abraham believed he had broken his had in round 7 and boxed sensibly for the remainder of the fight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ringside24.com/en/bout/5859/|title=Arthur Abraham \u2013 Nikola Sjekloca|work=ringside24.com|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ringtv.com/336823-arthur-abraham-ud-12-nikola-sjekloca/|title=Arthur Abraham UD 12 Nikola Sjekloca \u2013 The Ring|date=2014-05-03|work=The Ring|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-injures-hand-still-overcomes-sjekloca--77402|title=Arthur Abraham Injures Hand, Still Overcomes Sjekloca|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\n====Abraham vs. Smith I, II====\nPromoter Kalle Sauerland announced on 21 July 2014, that Abraham would defend his WBO title against English boxer [[Paul Smith (boxer)|Paul Smith]] (35-3, 20 KOs) at [[Sparkassen-Arena]] in Germany on 27 September.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ringtv.com/348583-arthur-abraham-to-defend-against-paul-smith-on-sept-27/|title=Arthur Abraham to defend against Paul Smith on Sept. 27 - The Ring|date=2014-07-21|work=The Ring|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref> Talks for the fight began in May 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-paul-smith-title-showdown-talks--77873|title=Arthur Abraham-Paul Smith Title Showdown in Talks|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref> Prior to the fight, Smith stated he had studied Abraham's loss to Carl Froch. Froch used Smith as a sparring partner before their fight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/smith-froch-showed-me-perfect-way-beat-abraham--79534|title=Smith: Froch Showed Me Perfect Way To Beat Abraham|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref> Abraham defeated Smith to retain his title in a controversial decision. The fight went full 12 rounds as Abraham won on all three judges scorecards by a wide margin (119-109 & 117-111 twice).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2212869-arthur-abraham-vs-paul-smith-winner-scorecard-and-analysis|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Paul Smith: Winner, Scorecard and Analysis|last=Sunderland|first=Tom|work=Bleacher Report|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-tested-decisions-game-paul-smith--82600|title=Arthur Abraham Tested, Decisions Game Paul Smith|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref> The scorecards were derided in some quarters for being too wide given the competitiveness of the fight. Many British fans in attendance booed the decision. Smith's promoter [[Eddie Hearn]] dubbed the decision a \"disgrace\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/boxing/11126278/Paul-Smith-robbed-in-fight-against-Arthur-Abraham-in-Germany-as-Eddie-Hearn-calls-judges-verdicts-a-disgrace.html|title=Paul Smith robbed in fight against Arthur Abraham in Germany as Eddie Hearn calls judges' verdicts 'a disgrace'|last=Davies|first=Gareth A.|date=2014-09-27|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingnewsonline.net/arthur-abrahams-wide-points-win-over-paul-smith-puzzles-boxing-media/|title=Arthur Abraham's wide points win over Paul Smith puzzles boxing media - Boxing News|date=2014-09-28|work=Boxing News|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThe WBO stated they would review the fight and decision, with the possible outcome being a rematch.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/wbo-confirms-plan-review-abraham-smith-outcome--82648|title=WBO Confirms Plan To Review Abraham-Smith Outcome|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref> In October, the WBO rejected Smith's request for an immediate rematch, however confirmed that he would stay in the top 5 in their rankings. Smith still believed that he would get another opportunity through a voluntary defence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/wbo-denies-smiths-request-abraham-rematch--83292|title=WBO Denies Smith's Request For Abraham Rematch|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/paul-smith-gutted-over-wbo-ruling-on-direct-rematch--83367|title=Paul Smith 'Gutted' Over WBO Ruling on Direct Rematch|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nBy the end of October, Abraham made the WBO aware that he could fight Smith again in the 2015. In December 2014, a deal was reached for the rematch to take place. The fight would take place on 21 February 2015 at the [[O2 World Berlin|O<sub>2</sub> World Arena]] in Berlin.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-smith-rematch-set-go-february--85063|title=Abraham-Smith Rematch is Set To Go in February|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref> With another win, Abraham was hoping to set up a fight with [[Felix Sturm]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/paul-smith-im-here-crash-abraham-sturm-party--87641|title=Paul Smith: I'm Here To Crash The Abraham-Sturm Party|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref> With 9,000 fans in attendance, the fight went the full 12 rounds as Abraham won via points on all three scorecards (116-112, 117-111 twice). Abraham was mostly dominant during the fight when he unloaded a barrage of power punches, and spent some time against the ropes, covering up, to keep himself becoming fatigued.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-tops-smith-this-time-convincing-fashion--87696|title=Abraham Tops Smith, This Time In Convincing Fashion|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2015/2/21/8082849/smith-vs-abraham-2-results-boxing-sky-sports-live-play-fight-full-war-rematch-unanimous-decision+&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk|title=Abraham vs Smith II results: Abraham edges Smith in thrilling back and forth war|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref> After the fight, Smith praised Abraham, \"I felt I left it all in there tonight, I'm not going home with any or many regrets. He shook me once or twice, he was better tonight (than the first fight).\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/boxing/news/12040/9726768/paul-smith-praises-arthur-abraham-after-second-defeat-to-the-german|title=Paul Smith praises Arthur Abraham after second defeat to the German|work=Sky Sports|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en}}</ref> The fight averaged more than 4 million viewers [[Sat.1|SAT1]] in Germany.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-smith-ii-draws-over-4-million-home-viewers--87715|title=Abraham-Smith II Draws Over 4 Million Home Viewers|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\n====Abraham vs. Stieglitz IV, Murray====\nAbraham fought [[Robert Stieglitz]] (47-4-1 27 KOs) for the fourth and final time on 18 July 2015 at the [[Gerry Weber Stadion|Gerry Weber Stadium]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia|Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany]]. The fight was billed as 'Final Showdown'.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-stieglitz-part-four-official-july-18th--90820|title=Abraham-Stieglitz Part Four is Official For July 18th|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> The WBO ordered the fight on 26 February, giving both camps 90 days to reach a deal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-stieglitz-ordered-fourth-time--87856|title=Abraham-Stieglitz is Ordered For a Fourth Time|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> A deal was reached by both camps on 9 April.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-stieglitz-reach-terms-fourth-bout--89538|title=Abraham, Stieglitz Reach Terms For Fourth Bout|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> Although having a 3-1 lead against Stieglitz, Abraham promised to win via KO to cement his place as the number 1 super-middleweight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-promises-ko-win-over-stieglitz-fourth-meet--90899|title=Abraham Promises KO Win Over Stieglitz In Fourth Meet|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> Prior to the fight, Abraham made plans to continue his boxing career for a further two more years before considering the possibility of retirement. In an interview, he said, \"I will not lose. I plan on continuing my career for at least another two years and then retiring along with my coach and my world championship belt. \" He also made plans to possibly unify the division.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-plans-continue-career-two-more-years--92999|title=Abraham Plans To Continue Career For Two More Years|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/abraham-wants-unification-bouts-stieglitz-part-iv--93216|title=Abraham Wants Unification Bouts After Stieglitz Part IV|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref> Abraham won via TKO in the sixth round. Stieglitz was knocked down in round 4 once but managed to pick himself back up. Abraham was ahead on three judges scorecards at the time on stoppage (48-46, 50-44, 49-45).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2015/7/18/8998881/abraham-vs-stieglitz-iv-arthur-abraham-scores-sixth-round-stoppage-to|title=Abraham stops Stieglitz in six, ends rivalry|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-drops-stops-robert-stieglitz-six--93653|title=Arthur Abraham Drops, Stops Robert Stieglitz in Six|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 October 2015, [[Matchroom Sport]] announced that negotiations were done for Abraham to defend his WBO world title on 21 November against 33 year old British boxer [[Martin Murray (boxer)|Martin Murray]] (32-2-1, 15 KOs) at the [[TUI Arena]] in [[Hanover]]. Murray was still looking for his first world title after being stopped late by world middleweight champion [[Gennady Golovkin]] earlier in the year in what was his third world title challenge. Murray was on a three match winning streak since. The fight went full 12 rounds as Abraham won via split decision (116-111, 115-112, 112-115). Murray lost one point for holding in round eleven, which did not affect the outcome. Abraham praised Murray during the post fight interview, \"I trained hard, have shed blood and sweat. I was technically and tactically the better boxer. But I didn't box against a punchbag. He is a world-class fighter, who put in a good fight and you have to acknowledge that.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/boxing/news/12183/10074978/martin-murray-lost-a-split-decision-against-wbo-world-super0-middleweight-champion|title=Martin Murray loses to Arthur Abraham in split decision|work=Sky Sports|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/34893084|title=Martin Murray fails to take WBO title from Arthur Abraham|date=2015-11-22|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2017-10-02|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2015/11/21/9776256/abraham-vs-murray-results-arthur-abraham-takes-split-decision-to+&cd=7&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk|title=Abraham edges Murray to retain belt|work=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>\n\n==== Abraham vs. Ram\u00edrez ====\nIt was announced on 18 January 2016 that undefeated #1 WBO [[Gilberto Ram\u00edrez]] (33-0, 24 KOs) would be challenging Abraham for the [[List of WBO world champions|WBO super middleweight]] in the co-feature bout on the 9 April undercard of the [[Manny Pacquiao vs. Timothy Bradley III]] card on HBO pay-per-view. The fight card took place at the [[MGM Grand Las Vegas|MGM Grand]] in Las Vegas, Nevada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingnews24.com/2016/01/arum-wrapping-arthur-abraham-vs-gilberto-ramirez-pacquiao-bradley-card/|title=Arum wrapping up Arthur Abraham vs. Gilberto Ramirez for Pacquiao-Bradley card|date=2016-01-18|website=Boxing News 24|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/dan-rafael/post/_/id/14762/notes-abraham-ramirez-fight-being-negotiated|title=Notes: Abraham-Ramirez fight being negotiated|publisher=ESPN}}</ref> All three judges scored the fight 120-108 for Ram\u00edrez, who became the first Mexican fighter to win a super middleweight world title. Ram\u00edrez won on the punch count by outworking Abraham in almost very round with a superior jab, a consistent mix of head and body power punches, and superior head and foot movement. Abraham slipped to a (1-3) record in the United States following the defeat. In the post fight interview, Ram\u00edrez said, \"I took to him a Mexican boxing school. He was a very, very strong puncher, but he couldn't take any movement. I knew halfway through the fight I was going to win the fight. I came here to make history, and I did it.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/15172826/gilberto-ramirez-dominates-arthur-abraham-wins-super-middleweight-title|title=Ramirez dominates Abraham, wins super middleweight title|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2016-06-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/media/index.php?title=Fight:2040449|title=Fight:2040449 \u2013 BoxRec|website=boxrec.com|access-date=2016-05-23}}</ref>\n\n=== Later career ===\nTeam Sauerland announced that Abraham would fight on 16 July 2016 in his first bout since losing his 168-pound world title on 9 April. Abraham would face 23 year old Tim-Robin Lihaug (15-1, 8 KOs) for the vacant [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] International [[super middleweight]] title at the [[Max-Schmeling-Halle]] in Berlin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/boxing/story/_/id/15635352/arthur-abraham-fight-tim-robin-lihaug-july-16-berlin|title=Abraham's July fight to come against Lihaug|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2016-05-23}}</ref> Abraham won the fight with a decisive TKO victory stopping Lihaug in round 8 to claim the title, previously vacated by Gilberto Ramirez.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2652460-arthur-abraham-vs-tim-robin-lihaug-winner-recap-and-reaction|title=Abraham vs. Lihaug: Winner, Recap and Reaction|last=Wells|first=Adam|access-date=2016-07-17}}</ref>\n\nEarly talks in October suggested Abraham and [[Martin Murray (boxer)|Martin Murray]] (33-4-1, 16 KOs) could meet for the second time in Monaco on 12 November 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-martin-murray-ii-play-nov-12-monaco--109361?|title=Arthur Abraham-Martin Murray II in Play, Nov. 12 in Monaco \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref> The fight was scheduled take place at the [[Monte-Carlo Sporting|Salle des \u00c9toiles]]. The fight was announced as a non-title bout, where the winner would be the mandatory challenger for the WBO super middleweight title, the same title Abraham lost to Gilberto Ram\u00edrez in April 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/17760743/heavyweight-contender-luis-ortiz-fight-monte-carlo-november-12|title=Heavyweight Ortiz to fight Scott in Monte Carlo|newspaper=ESPN.com|access-date=2016-10-10}}</ref> Abraham suffered an elbow injury in training which pulled him off the card. It was thought that a rematch would take place at a future date, however Murray would find another opponent for the Monte Carlo card.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingnewsonline.net/arthur-abraham-withdraws-from-martin-murray-rematch/?|title=Arthur Abraham withdraws from Martin Murray rematch \u2013 Boxing News|date=2016-10-26|newspaper=Boxing News|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-26}}</ref> Russian boxer [[Dmitry Chudinov]] would step in Abraham's place until he withdrew due to a virus, having Nuhu Lawal replace him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/martin-murray-dmitry-chudinov-november-12-monaco--110275?|title=Martin Murray Confirms Dmitry Chudinov Showdown \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|access-date=2016-10-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/boxing/news/12183/10652025/martin-murray-faces-nuhu-lawal-after-dmitrii-chudinov-withdrawal|title=Martin Murray faces Nuhu Lawal after Dmitrii Chudinov withdrawal|last=|first=|date=November 10, 2016|website=Sky Sports|publisher=|access-date=November 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Abraham vs. Krasniqi====\nThe [[World Boxing Organization]] ordered a purse bid to take place on 4 January 2017 in Hungary for an eliminator between Abraham, ranked number two and number three ranked two time light heavyweight challenger [[Robin Krasniqi]] (46-4, 17 KOs) with $300,000 being the minimum bid.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-vs-robin-krasniqi-wbo-purse-bid-on-january-4--112138|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Robin Krasniqi WBO Purse Bid on January 4 \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|access-date=2016-12-27}}</ref> On 14 January, an agreement was reached for an eliminator to take place on 22 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/culcay-vs-andrade-on-march-11-abraham-krasniqi-on-april-22--112647#sthash.TeCNy6ek.dpuf|title=Culcay vs. Andrade on March 11, Abraham-Krasniqi on April 22|last=|first=|date=January 14, 2017|website=Boxing Scene|publisher=|access-date=January 17, 2017}}</ref> A press conference on 19 February confirmed that the fight would take place at the Messe Erfurt Convention Center in [[Erfurt]], Germany.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fightnews.com/Boxing/krasniqi-abraham-set-april-22-394756|title=Krasniqi-Abraham set for April 22 \u2022 Boxing News|date=2017-02-19|newspaper=Boxing News|access-date=2017-02-19|language=en-US|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170220014808/http://www.fightnews.com/Boxing/krasniqi-abraham-set-april-22-394756|archivedate=2017-02-20}}</ref> Abraham constantly hurt Krasniqi in the second half of the fight on his way to winning a 12-round unanimous decision and once again earned a world title match. The judges at ringside scored the fight 118-110, 115-114 and 117-111 in Abraham's favor. Krasniqi started the fight well using his height advantage. The fight turned around when Abraham caught Krasniqi in round 6 with a right hand. This turned the fight around and put Krasniqi on the back-foot. Abraham spent most of the later rounds cutting off the ring.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-punishes-robin-krasniqi-wins-wbo-eliminator--115875|title=Arthur Abraham Punishes Robin Krasniqi, Wins WBO Eliminator \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.badlefthook.com/2017/4/22/15396900/arthur-abraham-downs-robin-krasniqi-in-germany|title=Abraham downs Krasniqi, Ramirez next?|date=2017-04-22|website=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==== Abraham vs. Eubank Jr. ====\nReports suggested on 1 June 2017 that [[Chris Eubank Jr.|Chris Eubank Jr]]. would make his ring return in July 2017 defending his [[List of super-middleweight boxing champions|IBO super middleweight]] title against Abraham in London. It is believed that Eubank Jr. was offered in the region of \u00a33 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vitalboxing.com/article.asp?a=4771|title=Vital Boxing {{!}} Eubank Jnr Set for Abraham Fight|last=Ltd|first=Vitalnetwork|website=www.vitalboxing.com|language=en|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref> The two potential dates discussed were the 15 and 22 July.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-vs-chris-eubank-jr-play-july-15-july-22--117172|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Chris Eubank Jr. in Play For July 15 or July 22 \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref> It would be regarded as Eubank Jr.'s biggest fight since his loss to Saunders in 2014. On 5 June, it was confirmed that the fight would take place at the [[Wembley Arena]] on 15 July and televised on [[ITV Box Office]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/19539049/chris-eubank-jr-set-two-weight-world-champion-arthur-abraham|title=Eubank Jr set for Abraham battle|publisher=ESPN|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref> The official press announcement was scheduled to take place on 7 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2017/06/06/news/chris-eubank-jr-v-arthur-abraham-announcement-delayed|title=Chris Eubank Jr. v Arthur Abraham announcement delayed|last=Abraham|first=Eubank Jr v|website=WBN \u2013 World Boxing News|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref> On 7 July, the [[World Boxing Super Series]] announced the winner would be taking part in the super-middleweight knockout tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/eubank-abraham-winner-join-world-boxing-super-series--118261|title=Eubank-Abraham Winner Will Join World Boxing Super Series \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-07}}</ref> At the Draft Gala in Monte Carlo on 8 July, Chris Eubank Sr., who represented both Abraham and Eubank Jr. picked undefeated Turkish contender [[Avni Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m|Avni Yildrim]] (16-0, 10 KOs).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2017/07/09/news/george-groves-chris-eubank-jr-likely-to-meet-in-early-2018-wbss-unification-clash|title=George Groves, Chris Eubank Jr. likely to meet in early 2018 WBSS unification clash|last=WBN|website=WBN \u2013 World Boxing News|access-date=2017-07-10}}</ref> At the weigh in, Abraham weighed 12st 1lb 5oz, which was 1lb 13oz over the limit. He was given two hours to lose the extra weight. Eubank Jr. weighed inside the limit at 11st 13lb 3oz. It was said that if Abraham couldn't make weight a second time, the fight would still take place in a non-title fight. Abraham made weight on third attempt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2017/07/14/news/shocker-arthur-abraham-fails-weight-for-eubank-jr-clash|title=Shocker: Arthur Abraham fails weight for Chris Eubank Jr. clash|last=Hewlett|first=Joe|website=WBN \u2013 World Boxing News|access-date=2017-07-14}}</ref>\n\nEubank Jr. won via a unanimous decision with the scorecards 120-108, 120-108 and 118-110. Abraham had little to offer, mostly in defence mode as Eubank Jr. outlanded and outpointed him. Eubank Jr. landed uppercuts throughout the fight, many single and some in combinations, with Abraham only managing to connect a few shots clean, but left little to no damage. Abraham suffered his second defeat in his last four fights.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/chris-eubank-jr-dominates-arthur-abraham-results--118554|title=Chris Eubank Jr. Dominates Arthur Abraham, Secures WBSS Spot \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/20074368/chris-eubank-jr-dominates-arthur-abraham-earns-spot-world-boxing-super-series|title=Eubank dominates Abraham, earns spot in World Boxing Super Series|publisher=ESPN|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2017-07-16/chris-eubank-jnr-unanimously-defends-his-ibo-world-super-middleweight-title-with-win-over-arthur-abraham/|title=Chris Eubank Jnr unanimously defends his IBO world super-middleweight title with win over Arthur Abraham|work=ITV News|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==== Abraham vs. Nielsen ====\nOn 13 March 2018, Danish newspaper [[BT (tabloid)|BT]] reported that Abraham and Danish boxer [[Patrick Nielsen]] could next fight, although there was no agreement, the bout was being lightly discussed. Nielsen was coming off a loss to British boxer [[John Ryder (boxer)|John Ryder]] in October 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-vs-patrick-nielsen-play-agit-kabayel-returns--126182|title=Arthur Abraham vs. Patrick Nielsen in Play, Agit Kabayel Returns|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-03-19|language=en-us}}</ref> On 19 March, the fight was officially confirmed to take place on 28 April at the Baden Arena in [[Offenburg]], Germany.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2018/03/19/news/arthur-abraham-v-patrick-nielsen-make-or-break-clash-set-for-april-28|title=Arthur Abraham v Patrick Nielsen: Make or break clash set for April 28|last=Ringside|work=WBN - World Boxing News|access-date=2018-03-19|language=en-gb}}</ref> On fight night, Abraham dropped Nielsen on his way to edge out a win via split decision after 12 rounds to win the vacant WBO International title. Two judges scored the bout 116-111 each for Abraham and the remaining judge scored it 114-113 for Nielsen. Abraham pressured Nielsen throughout landing heavy shots. Nielsen used good movement around the ring, catching Abraham with jabs and combinations, however lacked the punching power to keep Abraham at a distance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-gains-split-decision-patrick-nielsen-results--127638|title=Arthur Abraham Gains Split Decision Win Over Patrick Nielsen|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\n==Life outside of boxing==\nAbraham appeared in [[Cologne]], Germany for an exhibition match against entertainer [[Oliver Pocher]] on 24 October 2009 in a bouncy, castle-like \"ring\" and fought with huge, air-cushion-like boxing gloves.<ref>{{cite news |title=Oliver Pocher vs Arthur Abraham October 23, 2009 |url=https://archive.is/20120701163109/http://bleacherreport.com/gallery/Oliver%20Pocher%20vs%20Arthur%20Abraham?d=2009-10-23 |work=Bleacher Report |date=23 October 2009 |access-date=4 December 2011}}</ref> On 9 April 2010, Abraham took to the dance show [[Let's Dance (German TV series)|Let's Dance]] on [[RTL Television|RTL]] with partner Nina Uszkureit, but left after the first episode of the show in order to concentrate fully on his boxing career.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arthur Abraham steigt freiwillig aus |url=https://www.rtl.de/cms/arthur-abraham-steigt-freiwillig-aus-275403.html |language=German |work=RTL |date=16 April 2010 |access-date=4 December 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn the film ''[[Max Schmeling (film)|Max Schmeling]]'' (2010), he played a supporting role of boxer [[Richard Vogt (boxer)|Richard Vogt]], Schmeling\u00b4s last opponent. Just as in real life, [[Ulli Wegner]] was in his corner.<ref>[http://www.boxen.com/en/boxer/supermiddleweight/arthur-abraham.html Arthur Abraham] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407074132/http://www.boxen.com/en/boxer/supermiddleweight/arthur-abraham.html |date=2012-04-07 }}. boxen.com. Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref>\n\nGerman actor and producer [[Til Schweiger]] invited Abraham to act in his film ''Crime Scene'' (2013). Til and Abraham had been friends for a long time. Abraham played a pimp that is a leader of a gang that controls the shadow business in the film.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=hy:\u0531\u0580\u0569\u0578\u0582\u0580 \u0531\u0562\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0574\u0568 \u0576\u056f\u0561\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0576\u057e\u0565\u056c \u0567 \u056f\u0561\u057e\u0561\u057f\u056b \u0564\u0565\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0574 (\u0586\u0578\u057f\u0578) |url=http://sport.news.am/arm/news/14951/artur-abrahamy-nkarahanvel-e-kavati-derum-foto.html |language=Armenian |work=NEWS.am Sport |date=19 November 2012 |access-date=31 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nAbraham was among the panel of judges for the \"Miss Germany\" beauty pageant in 2012 and 2013.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=hy:\u0531\u0580\u0569\u0578\u0582\u0580 \u0531\u0562\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0574\u0568` \"\u0544\u056b\u057d\u057d \u0533\u0565\u0580\u0574\u0561\u0576\u056b\u0561-2013\"-\u056b \u056a\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0580\u056b\u056b \u0561\u0576\u0564\u0561\u0574 (\u0586\u0578\u057f\u0578) |url=http://sport.news.am/arm/news/17506/artur-abrahamy-miss-germania-2013-i-zhyurii-andam-foto.html |language=Armenian |work=NEWS.am Sport |date=14 January 2013 |access-date=31 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 January 2013, the RA Ministry of Diaspora hosted a presser for Abraham. Minister Hranush Hakobyan praised Abraham as a role model and awarded him the \"Poghos Nubar\" medal.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=hy:\u0531\u0580\u0569\u0578\u0582\u0580 \u0531\u0562\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0574\u0568 \u057a\u0561\u0580\u0563\u0565\u0582\u0561\u057f\u0580\u057e\u0565\u056c \u0567 \"\u054a\u0578\u0572\u0578\u057d \u0546\u0578\u0582\u0562\u0561\u0580\" \u0574\u0565\u0564\u0561\u056c\u0578\u057e |url=http://sport.news.am/arm/news/17249/artur-abrahamy-pargevatrvel-e-poxos-nubar-medalov.html |language=Armenian |work=NEWS.am Sport |date=9 January 2013 |access-date=31 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Photos: Arthur Abraham Honored By Diaspora's RA Ministry |url=http://www.boxingscene.com/photos-arthur-abraham-honored-by-diasporas-ra-ministry--61234 |work=Boxing Scene |date=9 January 2013 |access-date=31 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nAbraham sent a letter of condolence on the death of [[Vladimir Yengibaryan]] to his family.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=hy:\u0531\u0580\u0569\u0578\u0582\u0580 \u0531\u0562\u0580\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0574\u056b \u0581\u0561\u057e\u0561\u056f\u0581\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576 \u056d\u0578\u057d\u0584\u0568\u055d \u054e\u056c\u0561\u0564\u056b\u0574\u056b\u0580 \u0535\u0576\u0563\u056b\u0562\u0561\u0580\u0575\u0561\u0576\u056b \u0574\u0561\u0570\u057e\u0561\u0576 \u056f\u0561\u057a\u0561\u056f\u0581\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0574\u0562 |url=http://sport.news.am/arm/news/18547/artur-abrahami-cavakcakan-khosqy-vladimir-engibaryani-mahvan-kapakcutyamb.html |language=Armenian |work=NEWS.am Sport |date=1 February 2013 |access-date=1 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis family members call him \"Avo\", short for Avetik.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ashkhari Hayer: Arthur Abraham|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KaDftE3lo78|publisher=[[Shant TV]]|language=hy|date=29 June 2014}}</ref> Abraham married his wife Mary, then a [[Yerevan State University]] student, in 2015. The wedding took place in [[Armenia]] and was not publicized; he informed media of his marriage six months later.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hovuni |first=Mariam |date=8 December 2015 |title=Arthur Abraham: \"I dream of having three children\" |url=http://erit.am/news/en/6154 |work=Erit.am |access-date=8 December 2015}}</ref> His younger brother [[Alexander Abraham (boxer)|Alexander]] is also a professional boxer,<ref>[http://www.boxnews.com.ua/en/Boxer/10851/Alexander-Abraham Alexander Abraham \u2013 Boxer \u2013 Boxing news]. Boxnews.com.ua. Retrieved on 2012-01-14.</ref> and his older brother Christian owns a furniture shop.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thebiofile.com/2010/11/biofile-with-arthur-abraham/ |title=Biofile with Arthur Abraham |date=24 November 2010 |publisher=Thebiofile.com |access-date=25 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502164010/http://thebiofile.com/2010/11/biofile-with-arthur-abraham/ |archive-date=2 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nAbraham plans on opening a boxing school in Armenia following his future retirement.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arthur Abraham Back In Action On January 14th |url=http://www.hyefighters.com/2011/11/17/arthur-abraham-back-in-action-on-january-14th/ |work=HyeFighters |date=17 November 2011 |access-date=4 December 2011}}</ref> He will also have foreign-language classes for students at the boxing school, such as English and German, to help have success internationally.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arthur Abraham wants to marry in Armenia |url=http://www.tert.am/en/news/2011/06/17/arturabraham/ |work=[[Tert.am]] |date=17 June 2011 |access-date=4 December 2011}}</ref>\n\nHe received German citizenship in August 2006, while also retaining his Armenian citizenship.<ref name=\"aawcbym\"/>\n\nOn 21 September 2008, Abraham and fellow boxer [[Vic Darchinyan]] were honored by Armenian President [[Serge Sargsyan]] during a 20th anniversary celebration of the nation's independence. Both men were awarded with medals \"For the great services for Armenia\" of the first degree.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sukachev |first1=Alexey |last2=Lagun |first2=Inna |date=21 September 2011 |title=Arthur Abraham, Vic Darchinyan Honored in Armenia |url=http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-vic-darchinyan-honored-armenia--44016 |work=Boxing Scene |access-date=5 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Professional boxing record==\n{{BoxingRecordSummary\n|draws=\n|nc=\n|ko-wins=30\n|ko-losses=1\n|dec-wins=17\n|dec-losses=4\n|dq-wins=\n|dq-losses=1\n}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!{{abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Result\n!Record\n!Opponent\n!Type\n!Round, time\n!Date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n|53\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|47\u20136\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|DEN}} [[Patrick Nielsen]]\n|SD\n|12\n|28 Apr 2018\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fl